  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0f3a2c8c7b8f4d9c9d5a3d11d5f50101, type: 3}
  m_Name: PokedexChickadee
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: bird_chickadee
  commonName: Black-capped Chickadee
  scientificName: Poecile atricapillus
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 4ae1274fed4285e49a9f2b4b037eb737, type: 3}
  category: Bird
  habitat: Deciduous & Mixed Forests
  height: 12 - 15 cm
  weight: 9 - 24 g
  diet: Insectivore
  rarity: Very common
  shortDescription: A tiny, round bird with a distinct black cap and throat, known
    for its bold and curious nature around humans.
  behaviorNotes: Acrobatic and incredibly fast. Frequently hangs upside down from
    outer twigs to catch hidden insects.
  observationTips: Listen for their signature "chicka-dee-dee-dee" call. They are
    highly active and constantly on the move through outer branches.
  funFact: The number of "dee" syllables at the end of their call indicates the danger
    level of a nearby predator, more "dees" mean a higher threat.
  facts:
  - Every autumn, they replace dying neurons to expand their hippocampus, allowing
    them to remember thousands of hidden seed caches.
  - To survive freezing winter nights, they can intentionally lower their core body
    temperature into a controlled state of hypothermia.
  - They form stable winter flocks that act as a neighborhood watch, alerting all
    nearby bird species if a predator approaches.
